'''低空跳伞'''（{{lang-en|BASE jumping}}）是指从固定高处跳下的[[跳伞|跳伞]]或[[翼装飞行|翼装飞行]]运动，其英文名称中的{{lang|en|BASE}}是四个低空跳伞常见地点的首字母，分别为高楼（{{lang|en|building}}）、天线塔（{{lang|en|antenna}}）、大桥（{{lang|en|span}}）以及悬崖（{{lang|en|Earth}}）。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.basenumbers.org/ |title=BASENumbers.org |publisher=BASENumbers.org |accessdate=2014-02-03 |archive-date=2017-05-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517070848/http://www.basenumbers.org/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Sangiro |url=http://www.basejumper.com |title=BASE Jumping Resource and Community |publisher=Basejumper.com |accessdate=2014-02-03 |archive-date=2017-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815085600/http://www.basejumper.com/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>由于低空跳伞的高度很低，这一运动与通常的跳伞运动（从飞机上跳下）相比危险得多。在美国，低空跳伞被许多人看作是一项边缘的[[极限运动|极限运动]]。<ref name=ch-trib-thrill>{{cite news |last=Dizikes |first=Cynthia |title=BASE jumpers fall for thrill-seeking lifestyle |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2011-04-22/news/ct-met-basejumping-20110421_1_base-jumpers-thrill-arrest |accessdate=15 March 2012 |newspaper=Chicago Tribune |date=April 22, 2011 |archive-date=2011-11-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111122180025/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2011-04-22/news/ct-met-basejumping-20110421_1_base-jumpers-thrill-arrest |dead-url=no }}</ref>正因为其危险性，这一运动在不少地方被立法禁止，虽然仍有些地方允许进行低空跳伞。

